=== Paresthesias and Sensory Disturbances
<subsec:paresthesias>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Tingling, numbness, or "pins and needles" sensations
    - Burning sensations in hands, feet, or other areas
    - Electric shock-like sensations
    - Crawling sensations on skin (formication)
    - Sensations often not following anatomical nerve distributions

*Mechanism.*
Paresthesias reflect small fiber neuropathy, documented in many ME/CFS patients via skin biopsy. Small nerve fibers are metabolically demanding and vulnerable to energy deficit and oxidative stress.
